# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: StoryBeginnings | Scene: MeetingKateInTheGarden
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah slowly walked through the castle's garden. A thin blanket of snow covered most of the plants."
    new "Sarah slowly walked through the castle's garden. A thin blanket of snow covered most of the plants."

    old "She sat down on one of the benches, drawing Varga's cloak tighter around herself."
    new "She sat down on one of the benches, drawing Varga's cloak tighter around herself."

    old "Sarah offered to give the cloak back, but now, sitting in the snow-covered garden, she was happy he had been too polite to accept."
    new "Sarah offered to give the cloak back, but now, sitting in the snow-covered garden, she was happy he had been too polite to accept."

    old "She wondered what to make of him. Accomplished beyond his years, and still, seemingly embarassed for his lowborn origins."
    new "She wondered what to make of him. Accomplished beyond his years, and still, seemingly embarassed for his lowborn origins."

    old "Sarah had met enough nobility to know that titles were a poor replacement for a good heart."
    new "Sarah had met enough nobility to know that titles were a poor replacement for a good heart."

    old "A twig snaps behind her."
    new "A twig snaps behind her."

    old "Sarah spun around towards the source of the sounds."
    new "Sarah spun around towards the source of the sounds."

    old "Standing a little distance off is a woman with grey hair, and soft white skin as if she could fade into the snow."
    new "Standing a little distance off is a woman with grey hair, and soft white skin as if she could fade into the snow."

    old "Something about her seems...familiar."
    new "Something about her seems...familiar."

    old "Hey Sarah, been a while."
    new "Hey Sarah, been a while."

    old "Sarah stares at the woman, trying to figure out how she knows her."
    new "Sarah stares at the woman, trying to figure out how she knows her."

    old "Then, it dawns on her."
    new "Then, it dawns on her."

    old "Kate!!"
    new "Kate!!"

    old "Sarah jumps off the bench and runs towards the woman, leaping into an embrace."
    new "Sarah jumps off the bench and runs towards the woman, leaping into an embrace."

    old "I was starting to worry you didn't remember me!"
    new "I was starting to worry you didn't remember me!"

    old "Kate laughs."
    new "Kate laughs."

    old "Wow, I just...I can't believe this. It's really you."
    new "Wow, I just...I can't believe this. It's really you."

    old "Sarah takes a step back, still holding onto Kate. She eyes her up and down, almost as if afraid she isn't real."
    new "Sarah takes a step back, still holding onto Kate. She eyes her up and down, almost as if afraid she isn't real."

    old "You've changed so much..."
    new "You've changed so much..."

    old "Kate had been Sarah's closest friend in childhood."
    new "Kate had been Sarah's closest friend in childhood."

    old "Unlike Sarah, Kate had been born to a servant family, working in the castle, but when they were children, matters of class weren't important."
    new "Unlike Sarah, Kate had been born to a servant family, working in the castle, but when they were children, matters of class weren't important."

    old "They had explored every corner of the castle together, for years, they had been inseparable."
    new "They had explored every corner of the castle together, for years, they had been inseparable."

    old "Then, one day, Kate and her family were just gone."
    new "Then, one day, Kate and her family were just gone."

    old "Sarah had been devastated. She asked her father to find her friend, but after months had gone by with no news, she had to move on."
    new "Sarah had been devastated. She asked her father to find her friend, but after months had gone by with no news, she had to move on."

    old "Her father had tried to comfort her, telling her that this was not unusual for servants, to simply leave for work elsewhere, but Sarah had always kept wondering where her friend went."
    new "Her father had tried to comfort her, telling her that this was not unusual for servants, to simply leave for work elsewhere, but Sarah had always kept wondering where her friend went."

    old "And now, after years, she stood right in front of her."
    new "And now, after years, she stood right in front of her."

    old "Older by quite a bit, of course, but Sarah could easily identify the features of her friend and how they had developed into maturity."
    new "Older by quite a bit, of course, but Sarah could easily identify the features of her friend and how they had developed into maturity."

    old "You're one to talk...just look at you. I remember when you were as flat-chested as a boy."
    new "You're one to talk...just look at you. I remember when you were as flat-chested as a boy."

    old "Sarah felt herself turn red."
    new "Sarah felt herself turn red."

    old "Still as crude as always, I see."
    new "Still as crude as always, I see."

    old "Yeah, I missed out on all the classes on how to be a lady, sorry."
    new "Yeah, I missed out on all the classes on how to be a lady, sorry."

    old "Sarah looks at her old friend. All grown up, but it was like she never left."
    new "Sarah looks at her old friend. All grown up, but it was like she never left."

    old "Where did you go..."
    new "Where did you go..."

    old "Sarah's tone had grown more serious. Half a question, half an accusation. How could you leave me like that, she wanted to ask."
    new "Sarah's tone had grown more serious. Half a question, half an accusation. How could you leave me like that, she wanted to ask."

    old "Kate turned away, searching for the words."
    new "Kate turned away, searching for the words."

    old "We were friends, Sarah, but you didn't know everything about me. About my life."
    new "We were friends, Sarah, but you didn't know everything about me. About my life."

    old "Kate sighs."
    new "Kate sighs."

    old "But you're right, I do owe you an explanation."
    new "But you're right, I do owe you an explanation."

    old "My life wasn't the same as yours. My family didn't come from money..."
    new "My life wasn't the same as yours. My family didn't come from money..."

    old "I knew that, and I never treated you any differently for it."
    new "I knew that, and I never treated you any differently for it."

    old "Kate shakes her head."
    new "Kate shakes her head."

    old "No, that's not what I mean."
    new "No, that's not what I mean."

    old "She pauses for a moment."
    new "She pauses for a moment."

    old "When we were growing up, we were free to do as we pleased, but as we grew older, more and more was expected of us. You noticed it too."
    new "When we were growing up, we were free to do as we pleased, but as we grew older, more and more was expected of us. You noticed it too."

    old "For you that meant taking classes, riding horses, learning how to be a princess."
    new "For you that meant taking classes, riding horses, learning how to be a princess."

    old "For me, it meant that my parents began to expect me to start working. Preparing me for what I was going to be. A servant in the castle..."
    new "For me, it meant that my parents began to expect me to start working. Preparing me for what I was going to be. A servant in the castle..."

    old "Kate took a longer pause, struggling to speak."
    new "Kate took a longer pause, struggling to speak."

    old "And it meant becoming...a wife."
    new "And it meant becoming...a wife."

    old "Kate let her words hang in the air."
    new "Kate let her words hang in the air."

    old "Sarah noticed how Kate had lingered on the word wife. As if there was some special significance to that fact."
    new "Sarah noticed how Kate had lingered on the word wife. As if there was some special significance to that fact."

    old "My family was preparing me for a life I never wanted. Being a poor kid, that I could handle, but the idea of becoming like my parents. Slaving away in some castle, for someone else, I didn't want to even think about it."
    new "My family was preparing me for a life I never wanted. Being a poor kid, that I could handle, but the idea of becoming like my parents. Slaving away in some castle, for someone else, I didn't want to even think about it."

    old "A lot happened at home, and I never let you see any of that. I didn't think you would understand."
    new "A lot happened at home, and I never let you see any of that. I didn't think you would understand."

    old "Kate looked to the ground. She seemed ashamed to admit that she had thought so low of her friend."
    new "Kate looked to the ground. She seemed ashamed to admit that she had thought so low of her friend."

    old "I suffered through it, growing up, pretending like it wasn't going to happen. That if I ignored it, it wouldn't be real. That worked for a while, because when I was with you, it was easy to forget the rest."
    new "I suffered through it, growing up, pretending like it wasn't going to happen. That if I ignored it, it wouldn't be real. That worked for a while, because when I was with you, it was easy to forget the rest."

    old "Kate looked straight at Sarah."
    new "Kate looked straight at Sarah."

    old "And then, one night, they brought over a man. Must have been, twice my age. And they told me he had recently lost his wife, and that he was looking for a new wife."
    new "And then, one night, they brought over a man. Must have been, twice my age. And they told me he had recently lost his wife, and that he was looking for a new wife."

    old "Sarah felt her chest tighten as her friend shared her grief."
    new "Sarah felt her chest tighten as her friend shared her grief."

    old "He was rich, by my family's standards. He would take care of me, they said. I would be provided for. And though they didn't say it, with me out of the house, it would be one less mouth to feed."
    new "He was rich, by my family's standards. He would take care of me, they said. I would be provided for. And though they didn't say it, with me out of the house, it would be one less mouth to feed."

    old "Kate looked past Sarah."
    new "Kate looked past Sarah."

    old "Sarah could see Kate's eyes, they seemed suddenly vacant, as if Kate was lost in a deep memory. Not just recalling, but reliving."
    new "Sarah could see Kate's eyes, they seemed suddenly vacant, as if Kate was lost in a deep memory. Not just recalling, but reliving."

    old "As my parents were telling me all this, I could feel, somewhere in the root of my soul that I would never be able to survive a life like that."
    new "As my parents were telling me all this, I could feel, somewhere in the root of my soul that I would never be able to survive a life like that."

    old "Some people can accept the torture that life inflicts on them, carry that burden...endure. I just knew that if I went with that man, I would not survive it."
    new "Some people can accept the torture that life inflicts on them, carry that burden...endure. I just knew that if I went with that man, I would not survive it."

    old "And so, that very night, as I could hear my parents bargain my life away in the next room, I gathered what little I had, and snuck out the house."
    new "And so, that very night, as I could hear my parents bargain my life away in the next room, I gathered what little I had, and snuck out the house."

    old "Kate looked back at Sarah again."
    new "Kate looked back at Sarah again."

    old "I tried to go to you, I swear, I wanted to tell you everything."
    new "I tried to go to you, I swear, I wanted to tell you everything."

    old "Kate almost seemed to beg Sarah."
    new "Kate almost seemed to beg Sarah."

    old "But I knew that if I did, your father would have just had his soldiers bring me back. For months after, I cried, knowing what I did to you."
    new "But I knew that if I did, your father would have just had his soldiers bring me back. For months after, I cried, knowing what I did to you."

    old "Kate's eyes had begun to well up."
    new "Kate's eyes had begun to well up."

    old "Sarah embraced her friend and could feel the warmth of Kate's tears on her cheek, cutting through the cold."
    new "Sarah embraced her friend and could feel the warmth of Kate's tears on her cheek, cutting through the cold."

    old "Kate began to sob, and Sarah drew her friend in closer."
    new "Kate began to sob, and Sarah drew her friend in closer."

    old "After a moment, Kate regained her composure, and struggled on with her story."
    new "After a moment, Kate regained her composure, and struggled on with her story."

    old "After that, I wandered around for a long time. I lived off the kindness of strangers for a long time."
    new "After that, I wandered around for a long time. I lived off the kindness of strangers for a long time."

    old "One day, I was begging at a town square, when a band of soldiers entered the town."
    new "One day, I was begging at a town square, when a band of soldiers entered the town."

    old "Riding at the front was this man- Ooh Sarah, you won't believe me, but it was like the sun's light fell on him and lingered. He was radiant."
    new "Riding at the front was this man- Ooh Sarah, you won't believe me, but it was like the sun's light fell on him and lingered. He was radiant."

    old "Kate's voice had begun to pick up, full of excitement."
    new "Kate's voice had begun to pick up, full of excitement."

    old "A crowd of people gathered to watch them, and I couldn't keep away. I was drawn in like everyone else."
    new "A crowd of people gathered to watch them, and I couldn't keep away. I was drawn in like everyone else."

    old "He looked across the crowd and his eyes fixed on me. I could hardly hear him over all the people, but I saw his mouth move, and Sarah, I swear on our friendship, he called out my name."
    new "He looked across the crowd and his eyes fixed on me. I could hardly hear him over all the people, but I saw his mouth move, and Sarah, I swear on our friendship, he called out my name."

    old "This man I had never met before, he knew me, out of thousands, and called me to him."
    new "This man I had never met before, he knew me, out of thousands, and called me to him."

    old "Kate's eyes welled up again, but these were tears of pure ecstasy."
    new "Kate's eyes welled up again, but these were tears of pure ecstasy."

    old "I came forward and fell to my knees before him. He pulled out a sword, this one actually."
    new "I came forward and fell to my knees before him. He pulled out a sword, this one actually."

    old "Kate pointed to the sword on her hip."
    new "Kate pointed to the sword on her hip."

    old "And he threw it down in front of me."
    new "And he threw it down in front of me."

    old "He told me that I had found what I was looking for, and all I had to do was pick up the sword and swear my loyalty to him."
    new "He told me that I had found what I was looking for, and all I had to do was pick up the sword and swear my loyalty to him."

    old "And I did, Sarah. With all my heart, I swore to him that I would be true."
    new "And I did, Sarah. With all my heart, I swore to him that I would be true."

    old "Kate paused, gathering her breath from the excitement, she had been speaking so fast."
    new "Kate paused, gathering her breath from the excitement, she had been speaking so fast."

    old "His name is Vaelen, and he's the leader of a mercenary company called \\\"Brothers of Providence\\\". Since that day, I've served him as best as I could."
    new "His name is Vaelen, and he's the leader of a mercenary company called \\\"Brothers of Providence\\\". Since that day, I've served him as best as I could."

    old "Sarah had listened attentively to her friend."
    new "Sarah had listened attentively to her friend."

    old "She could understand Kate's motivations, but she wasn't sure what to make of the last part of her story. All she could see was that Kate seemed happy just telling her about it."
    new "She could understand Kate's motivations, but she wasn't sure what to make of the last part of her story. All she could see was that Kate seemed happy just telling her about it."

    old "Kate...I'm just so happy to see you again, and to know that you've been okay all these years."
    new "Kate...I'm just so happy to see you again, and to know that you've been okay all these years."

    old "Travelling around the world, every now and again, I would hear news from Rosanna, and I would learn you were doing good."
    new "Travelling around the world, every now and again, I would hear news from Rosanna, and I would learn you were doing good."

    old "It was unfair that you never had that certainty about me. Ooh Sarah, if I could make this up to you, I would."
    new "It was unfair that you never had that certainty about me. Ooh Sarah, if I could make this up to you, I would."

    old "Sarah shook her head firmly."
    new "Sarah shook her head firmly."

    old "Put all that behind you. Whatever there is to be forgiven, consider it forgiven. Seeing you again, on a day like this, it seems like fate."
    new "Put all that behind you. Whatever there is to be forgiven, consider it forgiven. Seeing you again, on a day like this, it seems like fate."

    old "Kate came closer and grasped Sarah's hands."
    new "Kate came closer and grasped Sarah's hands."

    old "I'll admit Sarah, it's not fate. When the news of your father's death came to me, I knew that I had to return, as sure as I once knew I had to leave this place."
    new "I'll admit Sarah, it's not fate. When the news of your father's death came to me, I knew that I had to return, as sure as I once knew I had to leave this place."

    old "I just had this image in my mind, of you, all alone in this lifeless castle, and it wouldn't stop tormenting me until I had set out on the road, back to you."
    new "I just had this image in my mind, of you, all alone in this lifeless castle, and it wouldn't stop tormenting me until I had set out on the road, back to you."

    old "Sarah squeezed her friend's hands."
    new "Sarah squeezed her friend's hands."

    old "I'm not alone."
    new "I'm not alone."

    old "The two old friends embraced."
    new "The two old friends embraced."

    old "Sarah broke away from the embrace, remembering her duties."
    new "Sarah broke away from the embrace, remembering her duties."

    old "I need to go back inside, I've been away for too long...poor Thomas, he's in there all by himself."
    new "I need to go back inside, I've been away for too long...poor Thomas, he's in there all by himself."

    old "I understand."
    new "I understand."

    old "Please, don't leave though. Stay, stay in the castle and come visit me. I'll ask the servants to prepare you a room."
    new "Please, don't leave though. Stay, stay in the castle and come visit me. I'll ask the servants to prepare you a room."

    old "Kate smiled at Sarah."
    new "Kate smiled at Sarah."

    old "Thank you, Sarah, that means a lot to me."
    new "Thank you, Sarah, that means a lot to me."

    old "Sarah waved to her friend as she went back inside. She ordered the servants to prepare a guest room and went back to the great hall."
    new "Sarah waved to her friend as she went back inside. She ordered the servants to prepare a guest room and went back to the great hall."

